    <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="eyebrow">Spatial Intelligence · Austin, TX · Working on 5 continents</p>
<h1>Geography is the framework. Behaviour is what we measure.</h1>
<p class="lede">Siege Analytics measures human behaviour through geography — for campaigns, nonprofits, trade associations, and commercial teams deciding where to act.</p>
<p><a class="button" href="/contact/">Request scoping</a> <a class="button-secondary" href="/services/">Explore services</a></p>
<h2>01 — The premise</h2>
<p>A decade ago, turning raw addresses into precinct maps was hard enough to be a business. Today anyone can ask a model for a choropleth. The map was never the point — the judgment is: which boundaries matter, which questions geography can actually answer, and what the pattern tends to signal next.</p>
<h2>02 — What we do</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fractional CTO / CDO</strong> — senior technical and data leadership without the full-time hire.</li>
<li><strong>Spatial Intelligence</strong> — where to open, who to reach first, which boundary actually matters.</li>
<li><strong>Polling &amp; Research</strong> — campaign-grade polling and focus-group method, pointed at commercial and policy questions.</li>
<li><strong>Political Financial Analysis</strong> — federal, state, and local money records, resolved across jurisdictions and matched to your lists. The engine behind <a href="https://elect.info">elect.info</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Data Engineering</strong> — the right tool for the size of the problem, from a notebook to PostGIS to Sedona.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="/services/">All services →</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
