  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[Services]]></title>
    <link>https://siegeanalytics.com/services/</link>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[dheeraj]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://siegeanalytics.com/?page_id=102</guid>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
<h1>A full-service data &amp; geography partner.</h1>
<p class="lede">From fractional leadership to precinct-level delivery — a commitment to technology at every scale, whether Pandas, PostGIS, or Sedona.</p>

<h2>Seven ways we work</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Software engineering</strong> — production systems, pipelines, and tooling built to last.</li>
<li><strong>Data engineering &amp; services</strong> — modelling, warehousing, and the routine administration too: cutting lists, building reports, standing up dashboards.</li>
<li><strong>Spatial intelligence</strong> — geocoding, boundary work, site selection, and turf.</li>
<li><strong>Polling &amp; focus groups</strong> — campaign method translated to commercial and NGO policy questions.</li>
<li><strong>Political financial analysis</strong> — regulated money records resolved across federal, state, and local jurisdictions.</li>
<li><strong>Fractional CTO / CDO</strong> — embedded technical and data leadership.</li>
<li><strong>Research &amp; strategy</strong> — the question behind the map, framed and answered.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Signature engagements</h2>
<h3>Tier 1</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Political financial analysis</strong> — money leaves a public trail across federal, state, and local regulated records. We resolve entities across jurisdictions and match them to your BI lists or voter files: who funds whom, where money concentrates, and what a spending pattern signals next. The engine behind <a href="https://elect.info">elect.info</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Boundary estimation</strong> — deriving accurate boundaries where official geography is missing, stale, or wrong. <a href="/work/boundary-estimation/">See the method →</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Tier 2</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Spatial intelligence &amp; site selection</strong></li>
<li><strong>Polling, focus groups &amp; ethnography</strong> — <a href="/work/polling-ethnography/">read more →</a></li>
<li><strong>Fractional CTO / CDO</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><a class="button" href="/contact/">Request a quote / scoping</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
