  <!-- ============ FEATURE: BOUNDARY ESTIMATION ============ -->
  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[Boundary estimation]]></title>
    <link>https://siegeanalytics.com/work/boundary-estimation/</link>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[dheeraj]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://siegeanalytics.com/?page_id=110</guid>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="eyebrow">Method</p>
<h1>Boundary estimation.</h1>
<p class="lede">When official geography is missing, stale, or wrong, we estimate boundaries from the evidence — points, activity, and known constraints — and grade our confidence.</p>
<p>The approach reconstructs a boundary as the region best supported by the data: cluster the points, respect the hard edges, and quantify uncertainty so downstream targeting knows what to trust. Delivered as a California hospital-districts proof of concept for Mautinoa.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
