  <!-- ============ FEATURE: POLLING AS ETHNOGRAPHY ============ -->
  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[Polling as ethnography]]></title>
    <link>https://siegeanalytics.com/work/polling-ethnography/</link>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[dheeraj]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://siegeanalytics.com/?page_id=112</guid>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="eyebrow">Method</p>
<h1>Polling as ethnography.</h1>
<p class="lede">A poll, at its best, is a disciplined way of listening — not a scoreboard, but a structured account of how people understand their own lives.</p>
<p>We treat survey and focus-group work as fieldwork: design the instrument to hear, not to confirm; weight to the world, not the wish; and read the crosstabs as testimony. The method translates directly from campaigns to commercial and NGO policy questions.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
